Merge - Class in mergesort
This class implements the mergesort algorithm for an Array; there are 3 main methods:
Merge() - Constructor for class mergesort.Merge
 
mergesort - package mergesort
 
mergesort(T[]) - Static method in class mergesort.Merge
This method takes an array of a Comparable type T and sorts it.
It calls another mergesort method which takes both the array and the range over which the array must be sorted.
mergesort(T[], Integer, Integer, T[]) - Static method in class mergesort.Merge
This method sorts the array over the specified range with the mergesort algorithm.
mergesort(Rectangle[]) - Static method in class mergesort.Merge
Same as Merge.mergesort(Comparable[]) in functionality.
mergesort(Rectangle[], Integer, Integer) - Static method in class mergesort.Merge
Same as Merge#mergesort(Comparable[], Integer, Integer) in functionality, differs from it for the same reason Merge.mergesort(Rectangle[]) differs from Merge.mergesort(Comparable[]) (see Merge.mergesort(Rectangle[]) for details)
